modules.description: This module provides operations to declare and manage typed configuration parameters and command-line arguments, supporting value conversion from strings to primitives (int, float, bool), collections (lists, arrays, tuples), optional values, and path types. It works with configuration parameters, CLI arguments, and future values, enabling use cases like parsing user-provided strings into structured data with custom delimiters, handling optional flags, and generating manpage documentation with enumerated options and structured parameter descriptions.

This module coordinates PowerPC-related operations with structured configuration management and logging, handling command-line arguments and typed parameters alongside progress reporting. It supports data types like formatted messages, string arrays, metadata strings, and configuration values converted from primitives to complex structures. Operations include parsing configuration inputs into typed values, logging disassembly progress with severity levels, and reporting errors with contextual metadata. Use cases range from decoding instruction streams with status updates to validating and applying user-defined settings from CLI arguments.
